President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of New Hampshire due to a severe storm and flooding that occurred from December 22 to December 25, 2022. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Funding will be available to governments and nonprofit organizations for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. William F. Roy has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations, and additional designations may be made based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.